@startuml
title Configuration Change Tracker - Domain Model

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

class ConfigChange {
  +Guid Id
  +string RuleType
  +ConfigOperation Operation
  +string TargetKey
  +string? BeforeValue
  +string? AfterValue
  +string Reason
  +string ChangedBy
  +DateTime ChangedAtUtc
  +Validate()
}

class ConfigDefinition {
  +string RuleType
  +string TargetKey
  +bool RequiresCriticalNotification
  +Validate()
}

enum ConfigOperation {
  Add
  Update
  Delete
}

class ConfigChangeService {
  +CreateChange(ConfigChange change)
  +GetChangeById(Guid id)
  +ListChanges(string? type, DateTime? fromUtc, DateTime? toUtc)
}

interface IConfigChangeRepository {
  +Add(ConfigChange change)
  +GetById(Guid id)
  +List(string? type, DateTime? fromUtc, DateTime? toUtc)
}

interface IMonitoringNotifier {
  +NotifyCriticalChangeAsync(ConfigChange change)
}

ConfigChangeService --> IConfigChangeRepository : persists and queries
ConfigChangeService --> IMonitoringNotifier : notifies on critical change
ConfigChangeService --> ConfigDefinition : resolves criticality from definition

note right of ConfigChange
Invariants:
1) Id is unique and immutable.
2) ChangedAtUtc is set once in UTC.
3) Operation=Add requires AfterValue and no BeforeValue.
4) Operation=Update requires BeforeValue and AfterValue.
5) Operation=Delete requires BeforeValue and no AfterValue.
6) RuleType and TargetKey are required.
7) Critical notification is determined by ConfigDefinition.
end note

@enduml
